

through the purest of deepened skies, a beauty unmatched by any such thing that had came before. The light round stones which increased 
in size, until finally culminating in a large spherical structure, with stairs leading into the dome. Pillars lined the sides of the 
wide stretching stairs that led into the structure, on the inside, which was a hall. 

She turned to me and told me the ways of our people: "we come before all that shall ever have been".
Our hubris was absolute, and so pure that its completeness could not even be rivaled by ourselves. How could this have been ? 
It must been foretold much longer before there was nothing, back in the days before day itself had come into existence. 



-----------------
Wiping the hardened dusk from my face I rose, peering out from the other side of the great wall. I could see where worst of the damage had been done.
panicked slowly creeped on her face and she tightened her grip on my arm, firmly tugging my arm in gesture to come back down to her. I refused, seeing the 
most immediate danger had subsided for the moment. A heavy, grey sky with sparse skies lied above, and particles wafted all throughout the air we breathed .
A haze now surrounded us and spread along the sheltering wall. The steady sound of heavy breaths, still on high alert, filled my ears. I began to feel my 
tattered clothes that clung to my body, as the arm desperately clinging to me tightened its grip. "We'll have to move" I whispered. Worried glances were returned. 
 